Onboarding Flow

Getting started
in seconds

A warm welcome & pet setup

New users are greeted with an illustrated welcome screen that immediately communicates PetMind's warmth and personality — "Only for real friends."

Selecting a pet type via large icon-driven cards (Cat, Dog, Exotic, Other) means users never need to type anything to get started. The choice directly personalises everything that follows.

  • Large tap targets for fast, error-free selection
  • Illustrated icons match the app's friendly tone
  • "I don't have a pet yet" escape route — inclusive design

Personalise what you track

Before entering the app, users choose which categories matter to them — Diet, Drinking, Sleeping, Health, Activity. The selected categories shape the daily recording flow, so it's never cluttered with irrelevant questions.

  • Modifiable at any time in My Pet settings
  • Reduces cognitive load for daily check-ins
  • Supports exotic pet owners with unique tracking needs
Core Feature

The Daily Recording Flow

Designed to be completed in under 60 seconds. Multiple-choice inputs eliminate typing. Users can skip any step. A satisfying completion animation rewards the habit.

Health Records

Data that tells
a story

Dietary tracking & smart insights

The Records hub gives a clear overview of all tracked categories — Summary Report, Dietary, Drinking, Health, Activity, and Temperature & Humidity. Each drill-down provides time-series charts switchable between Day, Week, Month, and Year views.

The dietary page surfaces trends like a 12% increase vs yesterday, alongside today's full meal log and personalised nutrition tips.

  • Export as veterinary report — shared directly with vets
  • Bar charts with time filters for trend analysis
  • Contextual tips and recommendations per category

Vaccination & medication tracking

The Health record page shows the overall health rating (75%) alongside structured vaccination schedules (FeLV, Rabies, FVRCP) and deworming history — with clear overdue alerts highlighted in red.

Users see at a glance what's upcoming and what's been missed, without digging through separate calendars or vet notes.

  • Overdue alerts clearly marked — "Overdue for 4 days"
  • Vaccination log with full date history
  • Export button for sharing with veterinary professionals
Pet Profile

Everything about
your pet, in one place

Pet management & full customisation

The My Pet profile page surfaces KitKat's core data — type, breed, age, weight — alongside linked diet plans and a direct path to full health reports. All info is editable in place.

The settings page gives users control over every aspect of the experience: Record Customisation, Device Connection, Colour Theme, Push Notifications, and Dark Mode.

  • Smart device integration — 2 devices connected
  • Diet plan management with plan A/B/C switching
  • Colour theme customisable to match owner preference
  • Reminder scheduling without leaving the app
Design System

Visual language

A cohesive design system ties every screen together — warm orange as the primary action colour, Rubik for friendliness and readability, and a clean light-grey foundation.

Design Principles

  • Tap targets minimum 44×44pt for accessibility
  • High-contrast orange ensures visibility in all lighting
  • Icons supplement all labels — usable without reading
  • One primary action per screen — no decision fatigue
  • Skip options on every optional step — low-pressure UX
Design Process

3 iterations to get it right

Each prototype was tested with real users. Feedback was collected, synthesised, and directly fed into the next iteration — no guessing, only evidence-based decisions.

1

Iteration 1 — Cartoonish Draft

A lighthearted, highly illustrated first concept aimed to make pet care feel fun. Usability testing revealed users couldn't identify the app's core functions from the home screen, and low contrast made key elements hard to see.

❌ Unclear main functions ❌ Low contrast interface ❌ Vague button labels ❌ Inconsistent colour palette
2

Iteration 2 — Structural Redesign

Rebuilt around a clear app flow with a prominent central Record button. Auto-timestamping reduced manual effort. Navigation was reorganised to communicate purpose immediately on landing.

✓ Central record button ✓ Auto timestamp ✓ Clearer navigation ❌ Visual inconsistency remained
3

Iteration 3 — Final High-Fidelity

Unified the colour palette around high-contrast orange (#F5820D). Standardised typography with Rubik across all screens. Streamlined daily recording to multiple-choice inputs with skip options. Added completion animation and achievement feedback.

✓ Consistent orange palette ✓ Rubik throughout ✓ Multiple-choice inputs ✓ Skip any step ✓ Completion animation ✓ Smart recommendations
Evaluation & Reflection

What we learned

Structured observation testing with real users surfaced both wins and opportunities. These findings directly inform our recommended next steps.

Observation Findings

  • Clean layout and intuitive icons were praised — users navigated efficiently without any instruction
  • Most tasks completed successfully during usability testing
  • Recording process felt too long and repetitive for a daily habit
  • Profile page confused users — unclear whether it was the owner's or the pet's account
  • No visual confirmation of active reminders — required extra navigation steps to verify

Recommendations

  • Add a home screen status indicator showing active reminders — no navigation needed
  • Shorten the daily recording flow — target under 30 seconds by merging related questions
  • Visually distinguish pet profile from user account with clear header labels and distinct icons
  • Introduce habit streaks and micro-celebrations to increase long-term daily engagement
  • Further AI personalisation — adapt recording categories over time based on usage patterns
